## Summary

Adds a SolanaDerivedAccount class to `@aptos-labs/derived-wallet-solana` for server-side and script-based signing using Solana keypairs.

## Changes

### New Features

- New `SolanaDerivedAccount` class that extends `AbstractedAccount` for programmatic signing
  - Allows signing Aptos transactions using a Solana `Keypair` without user interaction
  - Uses `tweetnacl` for Ed25519 signing
  - Supports the SIWS (Sign-In With Solana) envelope format for on-chain verification

### Re-exports for Downstream Consumers

Added re-exports to simplify usage without requiring direct dependencies:
- `createSignInMessage` from `@solana/wallet-standard-util`
- `getChainName`, `getEntryFunctionName`, `createTransactionStatement` from `@aptos-labs/derived-wallet-base`

## Usage
```
import { Keypair } from "@solana/web3.js";
import { SolanaDerivedAccount } from "@aptos-labs/derived-wallet-solana";
import { Aptos, AptosConfig, Network } from "@aptos-labs/ts-sdk";

const account = new SolanaDerivedAccount({
  solanaKeypair: Keypair.generate(),
  domain: "my-dapp.com",
});

const aptos = new Aptos(new AptosConfig({ network: Network.TESTNET }));
const response = await aptos.signAndSubmitTransaction({
  signer: account,
  transaction: await aptos.transaction.build.simple({
    sender: account.accountAddress,
    data: { function: "0x1::aptos_account::transfer", functionArguments: [recipient, 100] },
  }),
});
```



